":"text","text":" blessed the last part of Job’s life more than the first. He owned fourteen thousand sheep and goats, six thousand camels, one thousand yoke of oxen, and one thousand female donkeys. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:42:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He also had seven sons and three daughters. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:42:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He named his first daughter Jemimah, his second Keziah, and his third Keren-happuch. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 45:8","book":"Psa","chapter":45,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Sg 2:14","book":"Sng","chapter":2,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 4:30","book":"Jer","chapter":4,"verse":30,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 45:8","book":"Psa","chapter":45,"verse":8},{"label":"Sg 2:14","book":"Sng","chapter":2,"verse":14},{"label":"Jr 4:30","book":"Jer","chapter":4,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:42:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"No women as beautiful as Job’s daughters could be found in all the land, and their father granted them an inheritance with their brothers."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:42:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Job lived 140 years after this and saw his children and their children to the fourth generation. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:42:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Job died, old and full of days. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:8","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 35:29","book":"Gen","chapter":35,"verse":29,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 29:28","book":"1Ch","chapter":29,"verse":28,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 25:8","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":8},{"label":"Gn 35:29","book":"Gen","chapter":35,"verse":2